{
    "esm": "0.4.0",
    "metadata": {
        "name": "DahnekeHeatTransportCorrection",
        "description": "Correction factor β_q for heat conduction to a sphere, valid across all Knudsen numbers from the continuum to the free-molecular regime. Exactly parallel to the Dahneke mass transport correction. Computes the heat transfer Knudsen number Kn_K = 2κ/(c̄'n'_gas m_gas c_v r) and the correction factor β_q = (Kn_K+1)/(2Kn_K(Kn_K+1)/α+1). Migrated from Aerosol.jl src/dahneke_brownian_diffusion.jl:93.",
        "tags": [
            "aerosol",
            "dahneke",
            "heat-transport",
            "transition-regime",
            "knudsen-number",
            "thermal-accommodation"
        ],
        "created": "2026-05-21T00:00:00Z",
        "authors": [
            "Aerosol.jl contributors",
            "EarthSciModels migration (esm-03p)"
        ],
        "references": [
            {
                "citation": "Dahneke, B. (1983). Simple Kinetic Theory of Brownian Diffusion in Vapors and Aerosols. In Theory of Dispersed Multiphase Flow (pp. 97–133). Academic Press. Eqs. 5.6–5.7."
            }
        ]
    },
    "models": {
        "DahnekeHeatTransportCorrection": {
            "reference": {
                "citation": "Dahneke, B. (1983) Simple Kinetic Theory of Brownian Diffusion in Vapors and Aerosols, in Theory of Dispersed Multiphase Flow, Academic Press, pp. 97–133. Eqs. 5.6–5.7 — heat transfer Knudsen number Kn_K and correction factor β_q. Migrated from Aerosol.jl src/dahneke_brownian_diffusion.jl:93 @ c8c640bb (esm-03p).",
                "notes": "source_ref: Aerosol.jl@c8c640bb:src/dahneke_brownian_diffusion.jl:93\n\nUpstream DahnekeHeatTransportCorrection is an MTK @component with 7 parameters (κ, n_gas, c_bar_gas, c_v, m_gas, r, α) and 2 algebraic variables (Kn_K, β_q) determined by explicit equations with no time derivative — both purely observed.\n\nEquations (Dahneke 1983, Eqs. 5.6–5.7):\n  Kn_K = 2κ / (c̄'_gas n_gas m_gas c_v r)     [heat transfer Knudsen number, Eq. 5.6]\n  β_q  = (Kn_K+1) / (2 Kn_K (Kn_K+1) / α + 1)  [heat transport correction factor, Eq. 5.7]\n\nThe formula is exactly parallel to the Dahneke mass transport correction (mass_transport.esm), with the heat transfer Knudsen number Kn_K replacing Kn_D and the thermal accommodation coefficient α replacing the sticking coefficient δ.\n\nDimensional analysis of Kn_K:\n  κ [W/(m·K)], c̄' [m/s], n' [m^-3], m [kg], c_v [J/(kg·K)], r [m]\n  denominator: [m/s][m^-3][kg][J/(kg·K)][m] = [W/(m·K)]\n  Kn_K is dimensionless ✓\n\nLimiting cases:\n  Kn_K → 0 (large r, continuum):     β_q → 1  (no correction)\n  Kn_K → ∞ (small r, free-molecular): β_q → α/(2 Kn_K) → 0 (strong reduction)\n\nAt Kn_K = 1 with α = 1: β_q = 2 / (4+1) = 2/5 = 0.4 exactly.\n\nEvaluation order: (κ, n_gas, c_bar_gas, m_gas, c_v, r) → Kn_K → (α) → β_q. Acyclic dependency graph.\n\nTolerance rationale (model-level rel=1e-9): purely algebraic system with two explicit rational expressions in float64. Round-off is ~1e-15 relative; rel=1e-9 leaves six orders of headroom — same as capillary_penetration.esm with comparable arithmetic complexity."
            },
            "tolerance": {
                "rel": 1e-09
            },
            "variables": {
                "κ": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "W/(m*K)",
                    "default": 0.026,
                    "description": "Thermal conductivity of the suspending gas. Default 0.026 W/(m·K) (dry air at 298 K)."
                },
                "n_gas": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m^-3",
                    "default": 2.46e+25,
                    "description": "Number concentration of suspending gas molecules. Default 2.46×10²⁵ m⁻³ (ideal gas at 298 K, 1 atm)."
                },
                "c_bar_gas": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m/s",
                    "default": 500.0,
                    "description": "Mean thermal velocity of gas molecules. Default 500 m/s (approximate for N₂ at 298 K)."
                },
                "c_v": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "J/(kg*K)",
                    "default": 718.0,
                    "description": "Specific heat at constant volume of the gas (per unit mass). Default 718 J/(kg·K) (diatomic ideal gas, e.g. N₂ at 298 K)."
                },
                "m_gas": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "kg",
                    "default": 4.81e-26,
                    "description": "Mass of a single gas molecule. Default 4.81×10⁻²⁶ kg (N₂, M ≈ 28 g/mol)."
                },
                "r": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "m",
                    "default": 1e-07,
                    "description": "Sphere (droplet/particle) radius. Default 100 nm — transition-regime aerosol."
                },
                "α": {
                    "type": "parameter",
                    "units": "1",
                    "default": 1.0,
                    "description": "Thermal accommodation coefficient: probability that a gas molecule striking the sphere exchanges thermal energy fully with it. Dimensionless; range (0, 1]. Default 1.0 (perfect accommodation). Smaller α reduces β_q in the free-molecular regime."
                },
                "Kn_K": {
                    "type": "observed",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Heat transfer Knudsen number (Eq. 5.6): Kn_K = 2κ/(c̄'_gas n_gas m_gas c_v r). Dimensionless ratio characterizing the heat transport regime: Kn_K ≪ 1 = continuum, Kn_K ≫ 1 = free-molecular, Kn_K ≈ 1 = transition.",
                    "expression": {
                        "op": "/",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    2.0,
                                    "κ"
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "op": "*",
                                "args": [
                                    "c_bar_gas",
                                    "n_gas",
                                    "m_gas",
                                    "c_v",
                                    "r"
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                },
                "β_q": {
                    "type": "observed",
                    "units": "1",
                    "description": "Heat transport correction factor (Eq. 5.7): β_q = (Kn_K+1)/(2Kn_K(Kn_K+1)/α+1). Dimensionless; equals 1 in the continuum limit (Kn_K → 0) and approaches α/(2Kn_K) → 0 in the free-molecular limit (Kn_K → ∞). Multiplies the continuum heat conduction rate Q_M to give the actual rate Q = β_q Q_M.",
                    "expression": {
                        "op": "/",
                        "args": [
                            {
                                "op": "+",
                                "args": [
                                    "Kn_K",
                                    1.0
                                ]
                            },
                            {
                                "op": "+",
                                "args": [
                                    {
                                        "op": "/",
                                        "args": [
                                            {
                                                "op": "*",
                                                "args": [
                                                    2.0,
                                                    "Kn_K",
                                                    {
                                                        "op": "+",
                                                        "args": [
                                                            "Kn_K",
                                                            1.0
                                                        ]
                                                    }
                                                ]
                                            },
                                            "α"
                                        ]
                                    },
                                    1.0
                                ]
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                }
            },
            "equations": [],
            "tests": [
                {
                    "id": "default_parameters",
                    "description": "Default parameters (κ=0.026 W/(m·K), n_gas=2.46×10²⁵ m⁻³, c_bar_gas=500 m/s, c_v=718 J/(kg·K), m_gas=4.81×10⁻²⁶ kg, r=100 nm, α=1). Kn_K = 2×0.026/(500×2.46e25×4.81e-26×718×1e-7) = 0.052/0.042479034 ≈ 1.2241. β_q = 2.2241/(2×1.2241×2.2241+1) ≈ 0.3451. Transition regime.",
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "Kn_K",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 1.2241332983231208,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "rel": 1e-12
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "β_q",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.3450798590680775,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "rel": 1e-12
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "exact_analytic_transition",
                    "description": "Exact analytic test: when Kn_K = 1.0 and α = 1.0, β_q = (1+1)/(2×1×2/1+1) = 2/(4+1) = 2/5 = 0.4 exactly. Achieved by setting r = 2κ/(c_bar_gas×n_gas×m_gas×c_v) = 2×0.026/424790.34 ≈ 1.22413×10⁻⁷ m. Uses the nearby default Kn_K ≈ 1.224 ≠ 1.0 — instead this test checks the formula directly using n_gas=1.0, m_gas=1.0, c_v=1.0, c_bar_gas=1.0, κ=0.5, r=1.0, α=1.0 to give Kn_K=1.0 exactly.",
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "κ": 0.5,
                        "n_gas": 1.0,
                        "c_bar_gas": 1.0,
                        "c_v": 1.0,
                        "m_gas": 1.0,
                        "r": 1.0,
                        "α": 1.0
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "Kn_K",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 1.0,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "rel": 1e-15
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "β_q",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.4,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "rel": 1e-15
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "continuum_limit",
                    "description": "Near-continuum regime: r=1 mm (large sphere). Kn_K = 2×0.026/(500×2.46e25×4.81e-26×718×1e-3) ≈ 1.224×10⁻⁴ ≪ 1. β_q → 1 — correction is negligible. Confirms that large particles (continuum regime) require no heat transport correction.",
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "r": 0.001
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "Kn_K",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.00012241332983231208,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "rel": 1e-12
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "β_q",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.9998775866738355,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "rel": 1e-12
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "free_molecular_limit",
                    "description": "Near free-molecular regime: r=1 nm. Kn_K ≈ 122.4 ≫ 1. β_q → α/(2 Kn_K) ≈ 1/(2×122.4) ≈ 0.00408. Confirms the strong heat transport reduction for very small particles. The asymptotic formula α/(2 Kn_K) ≈ 0.004085 agrees with the exact β_q ≈ 0.004084 to within 0.03%.",
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "r": 1e-09
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "Kn_K",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 122.41332983231206,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "rel": 1e-12
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "β_q",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.004084387321960984,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "rel": 1e-09
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "low_accommodation_coefficient",
                    "description": "Reduced thermal accommodation: α=0.1 at default r=100 nm. β_q = 2.2241/(2×1.2241×2.2241/0.1+1) ≈ 2.2241/(54.45+1) ≈ 0.04011. Lowering α from 1 to 0.1 reduces β_q from 0.3451 to 0.0401 — roughly 8.6× reduction — because the 2Kn_K(Kn_K+1)/α denominator term grows tenfold. Exercises the α wiring.",
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "α": 0.1
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "β_q",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.04010864741742192,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "rel": 1e-12
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "conductivity_scaling",
                    "description": "Doubling thermal conductivity: κ=0.052 doubles Kn_K from 1.224 to 2.448. β_q changes non-linearly from 0.3451 to 0.1928, confirming that Kn_K is proportional to κ and that β_q decreases monotonically with Kn_K.",
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "κ": 0.052
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "Kn_K",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 2.4482665966462416,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "rel": 1e-12
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "β_q",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.1928069892724093,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "rel": 1e-12
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "beta_q_monotone_with_radius",
                    "description": "β_q increases monotonically with r (larger sphere → smaller Kn_K → closer to continuum). At r=10 nm: Kn_K ≈ 12.24, β_q ≈ 0.04072. At r=100 nm (default): Kn_K ≈ 1.224, β_q ≈ 0.3451. At r=1 µm: Kn_K ≈ 0.1224, β_q ≈ 0.8805. Confirms monotone behavior over two decades in radius.",
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "r": 1e-06
                    },
                    "assertions": [
                        {
                            "variable": "Kn_K",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.12241332983231208,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "rel": 1e-12
                            }
                        },
                        {
                            "variable": "β_q",
                            "time": 0.0,
                            "expected": 0.8804645668444205,
                            "tolerance": {
                                "rel": 1e-12
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ],
            "examples": [
                {
                    "id": "beta_q_vs_radius",
                    "description": "Heat transport correction factor β_q as a function of particle radius r (log sweep 1 nm to 1 mm) at default gas properties and perfect accommodation (α=1). β_q increases monotonically from near 0 in the free-molecular regime (r ≪ 100 nm) through the transition region (r ≈ 100 nm) toward 1 in the continuum limit (r ≫ 1 µm). The inflection around r ≈ 100 nm marks the transition-regime center where Kn_K ≈ 1.",
                    "initial_state": {
                        "type": "per_variable",
                        "values": {}
                    },
                    "parameters": {},
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "r",
                                "range": {
                                    "start": 1e-09,
                                    "stop": 0.001,
                                    "count": 61,
                                    "scale": "log"
                                }
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "beta_q_vs_r",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "Heat transport correction factor β_q vs particle radius r. Approaches 1 in the continuum limit (large r) and decays toward 0 in the free-molecular limit (small r). The transition is centered near Kn_K = 1, i.e. r ≈ 100 nm for default gas properties.",
                            "x": {
                                "variable": "r",
                                "label": "Particle radius r (m)"
                            },
                            "y": {
                                "variable": "β_q",
                                "label": "Heat transport correction β_q (dimensionless)"
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "beta_q_vs_accommodation",
                    "description": "Heat transport correction factor β_q vs thermal accommodation coefficient α (log sweep 0.01 to 1) at default gas properties and r=100 nm (Kn_K ≈ 1.22). At α=1 (perfect accommodation) β_q ≈ 0.345; as α → 0 the denominator diverges and β_q → 0. Illustrates that poor thermal accommodation strongly suppresses heat transfer even in the transition regime.",
                    "initial_state": {
                        "type": "per_variable",
                        "values": {}
                    },
                    "parameters": {},
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
                    "parameter_sweep": {
                        "type": "cartesian",
                        "dimensions": [
                            {
                                "parameter": "α",
                                "range": {
                                    "start": 0.01,
                                    "stop": 1.0,
                                    "count": 51,
                                    "scale": "log"
                                }
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    "plots": [
                        {
                            "id": "beta_q_vs_alpha",
                            "type": "line",
                            "description": "β_q vs thermal accommodation coefficient α at Kn_K ≈ 1.22 (r=100 nm, default gas). β_q drops toward zero as α → 0 (the 2Kn_K(Kn_K+1)/α term diverges) and reaches ≈0.345 at α=1 (perfect accommodation).",
                            "x": {
                                "variable": "α",
                                "label": "Thermal accommodation coefficient α"
                            },
                            "y": {
                                "variable": "β_q",
                                "label": "Heat transport correction β_q (dimensionless)"
                            }
                        }
                    ]
                }
            ]
        }
    }
}
